**GENERAL RULES**
Use this file to store all TODO's as requested.

Each item should be sufficiently articulated so that another AI with access to the project can perform the necessary actions.

After completing an item move it (prepend it) into the COMPLETED ITEMS section

If appropriate, make sure UI items will be documented, or their documentation will updated, by adding an AiReminder span. 

When considering this file, see if any ACTIVE ITEMS are completed, and need to be moved, and whether the RECOMMENDED SEQUENCE does not contain any completed items.

We don't need End-User documentation for some tsx files. Such as WelcomeModal, KeyMapPage, AutomatedTestsPanel, DocumentationModal,
or ClaimHint. 

When I tell you a file does not need end-user documentation, then update that file with a flag that tells you not to force it to be documented. 

COMPLETED items should be moved to the COMPLETED ITEMS section
